'.\" -*- nroff -*-
.TH KAFS-BACK 8 "2026-03-15" "kafs 0.3.1" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
kafs-back \- hotplug back process speaking KAFS RPC
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kafs-back
.RB [ --fd
.IR num ]
.RB [ --uds
.IR path ]
.RB [ --image
.IR path ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B kafs-back
connects to front side via inherited fd or UDS, completes RPC handshake,
and serves filesystem RPC requests.
.PP
When built with image backend support, an image path is required either via
.B --image
or
.BR KAFS_IMAGE .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR --fd " " <num>
Use an inherited connected fd explicitly.
This is primarily intended for supervised restart and testing.
.TP
.BR --uds " " <path>
Set UDS path when inherited back fd is not available.
.TP
.BR --image " " <path>
Set image path explicitly.
.TP
.BR -h ", " --help
Show help and exit.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B KAFS_HOTPLUG_BACK_FD
Inherited connected fd from
.BR kafs-front (8) .
When valid, UDS connect is skipped.
.TP
.B KAFS_HOTPLUG_UDS
Default UDS path.
.TP
.B KAFS_IMAGE
Default image path (when image backend is enabled).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR kafs (1),
.BR kafsctl (1),
.BR kafs-front (8)
.SH AUTHOR
kafs project.
